div.p: This document charts the progress made so far in collecting plant samples for the Darwin Tree of Life project. Overall, 245 specimens have been collected up until 03-Dec-2020.
Fig. 1 - the bar shows the current number of plant families collected, split by vascular plants and bryophytes. The target is 132 for vascular plants, and 128 for bryophytes (red dashes).
Fig. 2 - bar charts split by family, genus, and species which show the number of taxa collected at each taxonomic level.
Fig. 3 - the distribution of genome size variation in collected plants. Genomes greater than 25Gb excluded (2). There is currently a 494-fold variation in genome sizes collected.
Fig. 4 - spike map of Great Britain and Ireland, showing areas where samples have been collected so far.
Created by Max Brown, Lucia Campos-Dominguez, and Alex Twyford.
